<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.284507>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Tydeus narolicatus Kazmierski and Ripka, sp. nov., holotype female: (A) general dorsal view with five eggs inside; (B) fragment of dorsal striation with tubercles; (C) ventral metasternal region." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/284507/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.284508>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Tydeus narolicatus Kazmierski and Ripka, sp. nov., holotype female. (A) fragment of dorsal ornamentation; (B) cheliceral stiletto; (C) left palpal tibia and tarsus (adaxial view); (D) bothridial seta; (E) opisthosomal seta h 1; (F) coxal organ cg; (G) leg I: right tibia, tarsus and apotele (adaial view); (H) solenidion of tarsus II." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/284508/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

